Luis Andres Cuyun, 30, was the director of a jail for young gang members in Guatemala City . 
  He was riding in a car when two suspected Mara Salvatrucha members opened fire on him and his driver . 
  Salvadoran Juan Carlos Medina Luna, 29, and Mario Alfonso Aguilar, 18, were arrested after a police chase in the capital on Friday . 
  Medina Luna said he had come to the country to kill the director as 'revenge' for treatment of gang members at the jail . 
  He said he did the hit job 'because I like to kill' and was ordered to do it by a gang leader  . 
 